### 6. `src/commands/help.ts` — Show JSON fields in `sentry help <cmd>`

The `formatHelpHuman` function already renders `CommandInfo`. Extend it to render `jsonFields` when present:

```typescript
if (info.jsonFields?.length) {
  lines.push("");
  lines.push("**JSON Fields** (use `--json --fields` to select):");
  lines.push("");
  for (const field of info.jsonFields) {
    const opt = field.optional ? "?" : "";
    const desc = field.description ? ` — ${field.description}` : "";
    lines.push(`  ${field.name}${opt} (${field.type})${desc}`);
  }
}
```

### 7. `script/generate-skill.ts` — Include JSON fields in reference docs

In `generateFullCommandDoc(cmd)`, after flags and before examples, add a JSON fields section when `cmd.jsonFields` is present:

```typescript
if (cmd.jsonFields?.length) {
  lines.push("");
  lines.push("**JSON Fields** (use `--json --fields` to select):");
  lines.push("");
  lines.push("| Field | Type | Description |");
  lines.push("|-------|------|-------------|");
  for (const field of cmd.jsonFields) {
    const desc = field.description ?? "";
    lines.push(`| \`${field.name}\` | ${field.type} | ${desc} |`);
  }
}
```

